{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861721977,"sessionID":"ses_286651cc0ffe9uN3u4wA87KEd6","part":{"id":"prt_d799b6192001vZATo6Xsku27av","messageID":"msg_d799b42cf001edz2MhnheLsT6N","sessionID":"ses_286651cc0ffe9uN3u4wA87KEd6","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-735ae5bc681d47c4bf73e3c7b4802ef7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/execute.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/execute.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package picod\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"bytes\"\n5: \t\"context\"\n6: \t\"fmt\"\n7: \t\"os\"\n8: \t\"os/exec\"\n9: \t\"time\"\n10: \n11: \t\"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\"\n12: )\n13: \n14: const (\n15: \tTimeoutExitCode = 124\n16: \tdefaultTimeout  = 60 * time.Second\n17: )\n18: \n19: type ExecuteRequest struct {\n20: \tCommand    []string          `json:\"command\" binding:\"required\"`\n21: \tTimeout    string            `json:\"timeout\"`\n22: \tWorkingDir string            `json:\"working_dir\"`\n23: \tEnv        map[string]string `json:\"env\"`\n24: }\n25: \n26: type ExecuteResponse struct {\n27: \tStdout    string    `json:\"stdout\"`\n28: \tStderr    string    `json:\"stderr\"`\n29: \tExitCode  int       `json:\"exit_code\"`\n30: \tDuration  float64   `json:\"duration\"`\n31: \tStartTime time.Time `json:\"start_time\"`\n32: \tEndTime   time.Time `json:\"end_time\"`\n33: }\n34: \n35: func (s *Server) ExecuteHandler(c *gin.Context) {\n36: \tvar req ExecuteRequest\n37: \tif err := c.ShouldBindJSON(&req); err != nil {\n38: \t\tc.JSON(400, gin.H{\"error\": \"invalid request body\"})\n39: \t\treturn\n40: \t}\n41: \n42: \tif len(req.Command) == 0 {\n43: \t\tc.JSON(400, gin.H{\"error\": \"missing command\"})\n44: \t\treturn\n45: \t}\n46: \n47: \ttimeout := defaultTimeout\n48: \tif req.Timeout != \"\" {\n49: \t\tparsed, err := time.ParseDuration(req.Timeout)\n50: \t\tif err == nil {\n51: \t\t\ttimeout = parsed\n52: \t\t}\n53: \t}\n54: \n55: \tctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(c.Request.Context(), timeout)\n56: \tdefer cancel()\n57: \n58: \tcmd := exec.CommandContext(ctx, req.Command[0], req.Command[1:]...)\n59: \n60: \tif req.WorkingDir != \"\" {\n61: \t\tsanitized, err := sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.WorkingDir)\n62: \t\tif err != nil {\n63: \t\t\tc.JSON(400, gin.H{\"error\": fmt.Sprintf(\"invalid working directory: %s\", err.Error())})\n64: \t\t\treturn\n65: \t\t}\n66: \t\tcmd.Dir = sanitized\n67: \t} else {\n68: \t\tcmd.Dir = s.workspace\n69: \t}\n70: \n71: \tif req.Env != nil {\n72: \t\tcmd.Env = os.Environ()\n73: \t\tfor k, v := range req.Env {\n74: \t\t\tcmd.Env = append(cmd.Env, fmt.Sprintf(\"%s=%s\", k, v))\n75: \t\t}\n76: \t}\n77: \n78: \tstdout := &bytes.Buffer{}\n79: \tstderr := &bytes.Buffer{}\n80: \tcmd.Stdout = stdout\n81: \tcmd.Stderr = stderr\n82: \tcmd.Stdin = nil\n83: \n84: \tstartTime := time.Now()\n85: \terr := cmd.Run()\n86: \tendTime := time.Now()\n87: \n88: \texitCode := 0\n89: \tif err != nil {\n90: \t\tif ctx.Err() == context.DeadlineExceeded {\n91: \t\t\texitCode = TimeoutExitCode\n92: \t\t\tstderr.WriteString(\"command timed out\")\n93: \t\t} else if exitErr, ok := err.(*exec.ExitError); ok {\n94: \t\t\texitCode = exitErr.ExitCode()\n95: \t\t} else {\n96: \t\t\texitCode = 1\n97: \t\t}\n98: \t}\n99: \n100: \tc.JSON(200, ExecuteResponse{\n101: \t\tStdout:    stdout.String(),\n102: \t\tStderr:    stderr.String(),\n103: \t\tExitCode:  exitCode,\n104: \t\tDuration:  endTime.Sub(startTime).Seconds(),\n105: \t\tStartTime: startTime,\n106: \t\tEndTime:   endTime,\n107: \t})\n108: }\n\n(End of file - total 108 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package picod\n\nimport (\n\t\"bytes\"\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"os\"\n\t\"os/exec\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\"\n)\n\nconst (\n\tTimeoutExitCode = 124\n\tdefaultTimeout  = 60 * time.Second\n)\n\ntype ExecuteRequest struct {\n\tCommand    []string          `json:\"command\" binding:\"required\"`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/execute.go","time":{"start":1775861721958,"end":1775861721976}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861721979,"sessionID":"ses_286651cc0ffe9uN3u4wA87KEd6","part":{"id":"prt_d799b65b8001cGTYr0wuqvNQn9","messageID":"msg_d799b42cf001edz2MhnheLsT6N","sessionID":"ses_286651cc0ffe9uN3u4wA87KEd6","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-1237a24f2805472798af8bed8500b25b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/config.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/config.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package picod\n2: \n3: type Config struct {\n4: \tPort      int\n5: \tWorkspace string\n6: }\n\n(End of file - total 6 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package picod\n\ntype Config struct {\n\tPort      int\n\tWorkspace string\n}","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/config.go","time":{"start":1775861721962,"end":1775861721978}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861721981,"sessionID":"ses_286651cc0ffe9uN3u4wA87KEd6","part":{"id":"prt_d799b6a35001d0hU2W5ZHc5kEB","messageID":"msg_d799b42cf001edz2MhnheLsT6N","sessionID":"ses_286651cc0ffe9uN3u4wA87KEd6","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-56246d1453404e8b9fb3e1de6a555b6f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-014/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-014/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 Proposal\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Implement the Valkey storage backend for AgentCube session management, completing the `valkeyStore` implementation from its current stub state to a fully functional `Store` interface implementation. This provides an open-source, LF-supported Redis-compatible storage alternative with identical data model semantics.\n6: \n7: **Current State**: The `valkeyStore` struct exists but all methods return `\"store: valkey not configured\"` errors. The `newValkeyStore` function creates an uninitialized store without actual Valkey client connection.\n8: \n9: **Target State**: Fully functional `valkeyStore` using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` client, supporting all Store interface operations with ZSET-based expiry/activity indexes.\n10: \n11: ## Scope\n12: \n13: ### In Scope\n14: \n15: | Deliverable | Description |\n16: |-------------|-------------|\n17: | `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` | Complete `valkeyStore` implementation with actual Valkey client |\n18: | `pkg/store/store_redis.go` | Update `newValkeyStore` to initialize client from options |\n19: | `pkg/store/store_test.go` | Valkey-specific unit tests (mocked via miniredis or valkey-go mock) |\n20: \n21: ### Implementation Details\n22: \n23: #### valkeyStore struct\n24: \n25: ```go\n26: type valkeyStore struct {\n27:     cli                  valkey.Client\n28:     sessionPrefix        string\n29:     expiryIndexKey       string\n30:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n31: }\n32: ```\n33: \n34: - `cli`: `valkey.Client` from `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`\n35: - Key constants identical to Redis: `session:`, `session:expiry`, `session:last_activity`\n36: \n37: #### Method Implementations\n38: \n39: | Method | Valkey API |\n40: |--------|------------|\n41: | `Ping` | `cli.Do(ctx, B().Ping().Build())` → check for `\"PONG\"` |\n42: | `GetSandboxBySessionID` | `B().Get().Key(key)` → bytes; `valkey.IsValkeyNil(err)` → `ErrNotFound` |\n43: | `StoreSandbox` | `cli.DoMulti(ctx, cmds...)` with SETNX + 2× ZADD |\n44: | `UpdateSandbox` | SET with XX flag; check `resp.ToString() == \"OK\"` |\n45: | `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | `DoMulti` with DEL + 2× ZREM |\n46: | `ListExpiredSandboxes` | `B().Zrangebyscore().Key(key).Min(\"-inf\").Max(score).Limit(0, limit)` → pipeline GET or MGET |\n47: | `ListInactiveSandboxes` | Same pattern on `last_activity` key |\n48: | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | `B().Exists().Key(key)` → int64 == 1; then ZADD |\n49: | `Close` | `cli.Close()` |\n50: \n51: #### Configuration\n52: \n53: ```go\n54: func newValkeyStore(opts *valkeyClientOption) (Store, error) {\n55:     clientOpts := valkey.ClientOption{\n56:         InitAddress: opts.InitAddress,\n57:         Password:    opts.Password,\n58:     }\n59:     if opts.DisableCache {\n60:         clientOpts.DisableCache = true\n61:     }\n62:     if opts.ForceSingleClient {\n63:         clientOpts.ForceSingleClient = true\n64:     }\n65:     \n66:     cli, err := valkey.NewClient(clientOpts)\n67:     if err != nil {\n68:         return nil, err\n69:     }\n70:     \n71:     return &valkeyStore{\n72:         cli:                  cli,\n73:         sessionPrefix:        defaultSessionPrefix,\n74:         expiryIndexKey:       defaultExpiryIndexKey,\n75:         lastActivityIndexKey: defaultLastActivityIndexKey,\n76:     }, nil\n77: }\n78: ```\n79: \n80: #### Environment Variables\n81: \n82: | Variable | Required | Notes |\n83: |----------|----------|--------|\n84: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | Comma-separated → `InitAddress` |\n85: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` | |\n86: | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `\"true\"` → `DisableCache: true` |\n87: | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `\"true\"` → `ForceSingleClient: true` |\n88: \n89: ### Out of Scope\n90: \n91: - Redis implementation changes (AR-013)\n92: - Store interface modifications\n93: - Valkey Cluster TLS configuration\n94: - Data migration between Redis and Valkey\n95: - Connection pool tuning\n96: - Retry/backoff logic beyond valkey-go defaults\n97: \n98: ## Impact Analysis\n99: \n100: ### Upstream Dependencies\n101: \n102: | Dependency | Version | Impact |\n103: |------------|---------|--------|\n104: | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | Latest | Primary client library; provides `Client`, `ClientOption`, builder API (`B()`) |\n105: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Existing | Logging for connection errors |\n106: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | Existing | `SandboxInfo` struct for JSON marshaling |\n107: \n108: ### Downstream Consumers\n109: \n110: | Consumer | Method Usage |\n111: |----------|--------------|\n112: | Session Manager | `StoreSandbox`, `GetSandboxBySessionID`, `UpdateSandbox` |\n113: | Router | `GetSandboxBySessionID` for session routing |\n114: | Garbage Collector | `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` |\n115: | Heartbeat | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` |\n116: \n117: ### Breaking Change Considerations\n118: \n119: - **Behavior Change**: Current stub returns errors; functional implementation will actually work\n120: - **No Interface Changes**: Store interface unchanged; existing consumers unaffected\n121: - **Singleton Behavior**: `STORE_TYPE=valkey` will now produce working store instead of stub\n122: - **Key Semantics**: Same key patterns as Redis; switching providers preserves data compatibility\n123: \n124: ### Compatibility Notes\n125: \n126: 1. **Redis-Valkey Interop**: Same wire protocol; data stored by Redis readable by Valkey\n127: 2. **Valkey MGET Slots**: Comment in design.md notes keys should be in same slot; deployment must ensure consistent hashing\n128: 3. **Error Mapping**: `valkey.IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound` (matches Redis `redis.Nil` handling)\n129: \n130: ## Alternatives Considered\n131: \n132: ### Alternative 1: Use go-redis for Both Providers\n133: \n134: **Approach**: Keep single Redis client library; Valkey config just changes address.\n135: \n136: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n137: |--------|------------|\n138: | Pros | Less code; one dependency; Valkey is Redis-compatible |\n139: | Cons | Loses Valkey-specific optimizations (caching, pipelining); go-redis may lag behind Valkey features |\n140: \n141: **Decision**: Rejected. Valkey-go provides optimized client with built-in caching (`DisableCache` option) and better Valkey-specific support. Dual libraries maintain provider flexibility.\n142: \n143: ### Alternative 2: Shared Implementation Base\n144: \n145: **Approach**: Create abstract `kvStore` struct with common logic; Redis and Valkey wrap it.\n146: \n147: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n148: |--------|------------|\n149: | Pros | Reduces code duplication; unified ZSET logic |\n150: | Cons | Different client APIs (go-redis vs valkey-go builders); abstraction adds complexity for ~200 lines each |\n151: \n152: **Decision**: Rejected. Go-redis uses method chaining (`ZAdd(ctx, key, Z{...})`) while valkey-go uses builder pattern (`B().Zadd().Key(k).ScoreMember(...).Build()`). Abstraction layer would be more complex than separate implementations.\n153: \n154: ### Alternative 3: Single Provider Only\n155: \n156: **Approach**: Remove Valkey option; only Redis supported.\n157: \n158: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n159: |--------|------------|\n160: | Pros | Simpler maintenance; one client library; fewer tests |\n161: | Cons | Locks into Redis ecosystem; no open-source LF-supported alternative; limits deployment options |\n162: \n163: **Decision**: Rejected. Valkey is Linux Foundation project as Redis fork; providing both options gives users vendor choice without significant overhead (same data model, same interface).\n164: \n165: ### Alternative 4: Etcd as Alternative Backend\n166: \n167: **Approach**: Add Etcd as third storage backend option.\n168: \n169: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n170: |--------|------------|\n171: | Pros | Kubernetes-native; strong consistency; lease-based expiry |\n172: | Cons | Higher latency; heavier resource footprint; no native ZSET equivalent |\n173: \n174: **Decision**: Rejected. Session storage needs low-latency key-value with time-based range queries. Sorted sets are optimal; Etcd would require custom index implementation.\n175: \n176: ## Risks\n177: \n178: | Risk | Mitigation |\n179: |------|------------|\n180: | Valkey connection failure on init | Environment validation in `newValkeyStoreFromEnv`; return error before singleton assignment |\n181: | Client initialization error | `valkey.NewClient` may fail; propagate error to `initStore` → klog.Error |\n182: | MGET slot requirement | Add documentation note; deployment guide for consistent hashing |\n183: | Pipeline vs DoMulti semantics | `DoMulti` fails on any error; matches Redis pipeline behavior |\n184: | Builder pattern confusion | Use consistent `B().Command().Key().Build()` pattern; reference design.md |\n185: | Missing password validation | `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` must be case-insensitive `\"false\"` |\n186: \n187: ## Implementation Checklist\n188: \n189: 1. **Client Initialization**\n190:    - Import `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`\n191:    - `newValkeyStore` creates actual `valkey.Client` from `ClientOption`\n192:    - Remove singleton pattern inside `newValkeyStore` (use simple constructor)\n193: \n194: 2. **Ping Implementation**\n195:    - `cli.Do(ctx, B().Ping().Build())`\n196:    - Verify response equals `\"PONG\"`\n197: \n198: 3. **GetSandboxBySessionID**\n199:    - `B().Get().Key(sessionKey).Build()`\n200:    - `valkey.IsValkeyNil(err)` → return `ErrNotFound`\n201:    - Unmarshal JSON bytes to `SandboxInfo`\n202: \n203: 4. **StoreSandbox**\n204:    - Validate nil sandbox, zero `ExpiresAt`, empty `SessionID`\n205:    - Build SETNX command, 2 ZADD commands\n206:    - `cli.DoMulti(ctx, cmds...)`\n207:    - Check SETNX success (first resp `ToString() != \"OK\"` means already exists → `ErrSessionExists`)\n208: \n209: 5. **UpdateSandbox**\n210:    - SET with XX flag via builder\n211:    - Success: `resp.ToString() == \"OK\"`\n212:    - Failure: `ErrKeyNotExists`\n213: \n214: 6. **DeleteSandboxBySessionID**\n215:    - DoMulti: DEL + 2× ZREM\n216: \n217: 7. **ListExpiredSandboxes / ListInactiveSandboxes**\n218:    - `B().Zrangebyscore().Key(indexKey).Min(\"-inf\").Max(before.Unix()).Limit(0, limit).Build()`\n219:    - Parse session IDs from response\n220:    - Build keys; use MGET for batch retrieval\n221:    - Skip missing keys (tolerate `IsValkeyNil`)\n222:    - Unmarshal valid entries\n223: \n224: 8. **UpdateSessionLastActivity**\n225:    - `B().Exists().Key(sessionKey).Build()` → int64 == 1\n226:    - If missing → `ErrNotFound`\n227:    - `B().Zadd().Key(lastActivityKey).ScoreMember(score, sessionID).Build()`\n228: \n229: 9. **Close**\n230:    - `cli.Close()`; return nil\n231: \n232: 10. **Tests**\n233:     - Use miniredis (Redis-compatible mock) for functional tests\n234:     - Or use valkey-go's mock capabilities\n235:     - Test all methods; mirror Redis test patterns\n236: \n237: ## References\n238: \n239: - `session-store/design.md` — Valkey implementation specification (lines 395-452)\n240: - `session-store/spec.md` — Requirements: Valkey environment, ZSET semantics\n241: - `changes/AR-013/proposal.md` — Redis implementation reference\n242: - `pkg/store/store_redis.go` — Redis implementation pattern to follow\n243: - [valkey-go documentation](https://github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go)\n244: - [Valkey project](https://valkey.io/)\n\n(End of file - total 244 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the Valkey storage backend for AgentCube session management, completing the `valkeyStore` implementation from its current stub state to a fully functional `Store` interface implementation. This provides an open-source, LF-supported Redis-compatible storage alternative with identical data model semantics.\n\n**Current State**: The `valkeyStore` struct exists but all methods return `\"store: valkey not configured\"` errors. The `newValkeyStore` function creates an uninitialized store without actual Valkey client connection.\n\n**Target State**: Fully functional `valkeyStore` using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` client, supporting all Store interface operations with ZSET-based expiry/activity indexes.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` | Complete `valkeyStore` implementation with actual Valkey client |\n| `pkg/store/store_redis.go` | Update `newValkeyStore` to initialize client from options |\n| `pkg/store/store_test.go` | Valkey-specific unit tests (mocked via miniredis or valkey-go mock) |\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-014/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775861721964,"end":1775861721979}}}}
