{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861817885,"sessionID":"ses_286651cc0ffe9uN3u4wA87KEd6","part":{"id":"prt_d799ce1e2001BEimtFw2X5G0XJ","messageID":"msg_d799b9889001Gn97EhybkeorPT","sessionID":"ses_286651cc0ffe9uN3u4wA87KEd6","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-abb79728b41b49408ec864de512ee61f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/proposal.md","content":"# AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nExtend PicoD's file management capabilities beyond the basic upload, list, and download operations implemented in AR-015. This adds comprehensive file system manipulation APIs including file deletion, directory creation, file copy/move, permissions modification, and archive operations (tar/zip) for AI agent workspace management.\n\n**Current State**: PicoD (AR-015) provides basic file operations: `POST /api/files` (upload), `GET /api/files?path=...` (list), `GET /api/files/*path` (download). Missing: deletion, directory creation, copy/move, permissions change, and archive handling.\n\n**Target State**: Full-featured file management API suite:\n- `DELETE /api/files/*path` — Delete files and directories\n- `POST /api/files/directory` — Create directories with optional mode\n- `POST /api/files/copy` — Copy files/directories within workspace\n- `POST /api/files/move` — Move/rename files/directories\n- `PATCH /api/files/*path` — Modify file permissions\n- `POST /api/files/archive` — Create tar/zip archives\n- `POST /api/files/extract` — Extract tar/zip archives\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/picod/files.go` (extend) | Add DeleteFileHandler, CreateDirectoryHandler, CopyFileHandler, MoveFileHandler, ModifyPermissionsHandler |\n| `pkg/picod/archive.go` | New file: ArchiveHandler, ExtractHandler with tar/zip support |\n| `pkg/picod/files.go` structs | DeleteRequest, CreateDirectoryRequest, CopyRequest, MoveRequest, ModifyPermissionsRequest, ArchiveRequest, ExtractRequest |\n| `pkg/picod/server.go` (extend) | Register new file management routes |\n| `pkg/picod/picod_test.go` (extend) | Unit tests for all new handlers |\n\n### Implementation Details\n\n#### Request/Response Structures\n\n**Delete**:\n```go\ntype DeleteRequest struct {\n    Path      string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n    Recursive bool   `json:\"recursive\"` // For directory deletion\n}\n\ntype DeleteResponse struct {\n    Path   string `json:\"path\"`\n    Deleted bool  `json:\"deleted\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Create Directory**:\n```go\ntype CreateDirectoryRequest struct {\n    Path string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n    Mode string `json:\"mode\"` // Octal, default 0755\n}\n\ntype CreateDirectoryResponse struct {\n    Path     string    `json:\"path\"`\n    Mode     string    `json:\"mode\"`\n    Created  bool      `json:\"created\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Copy**:\n```go\ntype CopyRequest struct {\n    Source string `json:\"source\" binding:\"required\"`\n    Dest   string `json:\"dest\" binding:\"required\"`\n}\n\ntype CopyResponse struct {\n    Source string `json:\"source\"`\n    Dest   string `json:\"dest\"`\n    Copied bool   `json:\"copied\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Move**:\n```go\ntype MoveRequest struct {\n    Source string `json:\"source\" binding:\"required\"`\n    Dest   string `json:\"dest\" binding:\"required\"`\n}\n\ntype MoveResponse struct {\n    Source string `json:\"source\"`\n    Dest   string `json:\"dest\"`\n    Moved  bool   `json:\"moved\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Modify Permissions**:\n```go\ntype ModifyPermissionsRequest struct {\n    Path string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n    Mode string `json:\"mode\" binding:\"required\"` // Octal\n}\n\ntype ModifyPermissionsResponse struct {\n    Path     string    `json:\"path\"`\n    OldMode  string    `json:\"old_mode\"`\n    NewMode  string    `json:\"new_mode\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Archive**:\n```go\ntype ArchiveRequest struct {\n    SourcePath string `json:\"source_path\" binding:\"required\"` // Directory or file to archive\n    DestPath   string `json:\"dest_path\" binding:\"required\"`   // Output archive path\n    Format     string `json:\"format\"`                         // \"tar\" or \"zip\", default \"tar\"\n}\n\ntype ArchiveResponse struct {\n    SourcePath string `json:\"source_path\"`\n    DestPath   string `json:\"dest_path\"`\n    Format     string `json:\"format\"`\n    Size       int64  `json:\"size\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Extract**:\n```go\ntype ExtractRequest struct {\n    SourcePath string `json:\"source_path\" binding:\"required\"` // Archive to extract\n    DestPath   string `json:\"dest_path\"`                      // Destination directory, defaults to archive parent\n}\n\ntype ExtractResponse struct {\n    SourcePath string     `json:\"source_path\"`\n    DestPath   string     `json:\"dest_path\"`\n    Files      []FileEntry `json:\"files\"` // Extracted files list\n}\n```\n\n#### Route Registration Extension\n\n```go\napi.DELETE(\"/files/*path\", s.DeleteFileHandler)\napi.POST(\"/files/directory\", s.CreateDirectoryHandler)\napi.POST(\"/files/copy\", s.CopyFileHandler)\napi.POST(\"/files/move\", s.MoveFileHandler)\napi.PATCH(\"/files/*path\", s.ModifyPermissionsHandler)\napi.POST(\"/files/archive\", s.ArchiveHandler)\napi.POST(\"/files/extract\", s.ExtractHandler)\n```\n\n#### Handler Implementations\n\n| Handler | Logic |\n|---------|-------|\n| `DeleteFileHandler` | Wildcard path; `os.Stat` to check if file or dir; file: `os.Remove`; dir: `os.RemoveAll` if recursive, else error if non-empty |\n| `CreateDirectoryHandler` | JSON bind; sanitize; `parseFileMode`; `os.MkdirAll`; return created status |\n| `CopyFileHandler` | Sanitize source/dest; `os.Stat` source; file: `io.Copy`; dir: recursive copy via `filepath.Walk` |\n| `MoveFileHandler` | Sanitize source/dest; `os.Rename`; handles cross-directory moves |\n| `ModifyPermissionsHandler` | Wildcard path; `os.Chmod` with parsed mode; return old/new mode |\n| `ArchiveHandler` | Sanitize paths; `archive/tar` or `archive/zip`; walk source, add entries; write to dest |\n| `ExtractHandler` | Sanitize paths; detect format by extension or request field; `tar.NewReader` or `zip.OpenReader`; extract each entry |\n\n#### Constants\n\n| Name | Value | Purpose |\n|------|-------|---------|\n| `defaultDirMode` | `0755` | Default directory creation mode |\n| `maxArchiveSize` | `100 << 20` (100 MiB) | Maximum archive size for extraction safety |\n| `allowedArchiveFormats` | `[\"tar\", \"zip\", \"tar.gz\", \"tgz\"]` | Supported archive formats |\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Symlink creation/resolution API (separate security concerns)\n- Multiple workspace roots\n- File content search/grep API\n- File locking/concurrent access control\n- Chunked/streaming large file operations\n- Remote file URLs (no external fetch)\n- File checksum verification (MD5/SHA)\n- Quarantine/sandbox escape detection beyond existing sanitizePath\n- Recursive permission modification\n- File ownership change (chown)\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Upstream Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Impact |\n|------------|---------|--------|\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | v1.10+ | HTTP framework; existing from AR-015 |\n| `archive/tar` | Standard | Tar archive creation/extraction |\n| `archive/zip` | Standard | Zip archive creation/extraction |\n| `compress/gzip` | Standard | Gzip compression for tar.gz |\n| `io` | Standard | Stream copying for file operations |\n| `filepath` | Standard | Path walking for recursive operations |\n| `os` | Standard | File system operations |\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n| Consumer | Method Usage |\n|----------|--------------|\n| CodeInterpreter Sandbox Pods | Directory creation for output folders; archive extraction for uploaded packages; cleanup via delete |\n| Agent Runtime Sandbox Pods | Move/rename for artifact organization; copy for backup; permissions for security staging |\n| Python SDK | Full file manipulation API calls; archive handling for dataset uploads |\n| Router | No direct impact; JWT auth unchanged |\n\n### Breaking Change Considerations\n\n- **New Routes Only**: All additions are new routes; no existing endpoints modified\n- **Backward Compatible**: AR-015 file APIs remain unchanged\n- **Behavioral Consistency**: Same sanitizePath security applied to all new operations\n- **Archive Format**: Only tar/zip supported; other formats rejected with error\n\n### Compatibility Notes\n\n1. **Path Security**: All new operations use existing `sanitizePath` for workspace jail enforcement\n2. **Recursive Operations**: Delete/copy with recursive flag; explicit flag prevents accidental mass deletion\n3. **Archive Paths**: Archive extraction validates each entry path against workspace jail\n4. **Move Semantics**: `os.Rename` may fail across filesystem boundaries; error returned if unsupported\n5. **Permissions Octal**: Same `parseFileMode` pattern as upload; octal string input\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Single Multi-Operation Endpoint\n\n**Approach**: `POST /api/files/operation` with `operation` field specifying copy/move/delete/etc.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Single endpoint; consistent request structure |\n| Cons | Less RESTful; harder to document; mixed error handling |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Separate endpoints follow REST conventions, enable granular error handling, and match existing PicoD API style.\n\n### Alternative 2: External Archive Tools\n\n**Approach**: Use `tar`/`zip` CLI commands via `exec.CommandContext` for archive operations.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Leverages well-tested tools; supports all formats |\n| Cons | Depends on container having tools installed; security via command execution; less portable |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Native Go `archive/tar` and `archive/zip` libraries are cross-platform, don't require container dependencies, and integrate with existing sanitization logic.\n\n### Alternative 3: File Operations via Command Execution\n\n**Approach**: Users implement file operations via `POST /api/execute` with shell commands (`rm`, `mkdir`, `cp`, `mv`).\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | No new code; maximum flexibility |\n| Cons | Shell-dependent; less secure; no structured error responses; harder to audit |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Dedicated API endpoints provide structured responses, consistent path security, and audit-friendly operation logs.\n\n### Alternative 4: WebDAV Protocol\n\n**Approach**: Expose WebDAV server for file operations (PROPFIND, COPY, MOVE, DELETE).\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Standard protocol; existing client libraries; directory listing built-in |\n| Cons | Different auth integration; more complex middleware; not JSON-based |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. REST/JSON API matches PicoD's existing design and Router integration. WebDAV would require separate auth handling and different middleware stack.\n\n### Alternative 5: Batch Operations Endpoint\n\n**Approach**: `POST /api/files/batch` accepting array of operations in single request.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Reduced round trips; atomic grouping |\n| Cons | Complex error handling; partial failure semantics unclear |\n\n**Decision**: Deferred. Batch operations are valuable but add complexity. Initial implementation uses single-operation endpoints; batch can be added later without breaking changes.\n\n## Risks\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| Recursive delete destroys workspace | `Recursive` flag required for directory deletion; non-empty dir without flag returns error |\n| Archive extraction path escape | Validate each archive entry path via `sanitizePath`; reject entries attempting `..` escape |\n| Large archive DoS | `maxArchiveSize` = 100 MiB; reject archives exceeding limit; streaming extraction avoids memory exhaustion |\n| Copy infinite loop (circular symlink) | `sanitizePath` resolves symlinks; skip symlinks in recursive copy or resolve target first |\n| Move across filesystem boundaries | `os.Rename` returns specific error; handler detects and returns appropriate message |\n| Concurrent modification conflict | No locking; operations are atomic at OS level; last-write-wins semantics |\n| Permission change security | Mode limited to `<= 0777`; same `parseFileMode` validation as upload |\n| Archive format confusion | Detect format by file extension + request field; reject unsupported formats |\n\n## Implementation Checklist\n\n1. **Delete Handler**\n   - Wildcard path extraction\n   - `os.Stat` to determine type\n   - File: `os.Remove`\n   - Directory: check `recursive` flag; `os.RemoveAll` or error if non-empty\n\n2. **Create Directory Handler**\n   - JSON bind `CreateDirectoryRequest`\n   - Sanitize path; `parseFileMode` (default 0755)\n   - `os.MkdirAll` for nested creation\n   - Return `CreateDirectoryResponse`\n\n3. **Copy Handler**\n   - Sanitize source and dest\n   - `os.Stat` source; detect file vs dir\n   - File: `os.Open` + `io.Copy`\n   - Directory: `filepath.Walk` with recursive copy\n\n4. **Move Handler**\n   - Sanitize source and dest\n   - `os.Rename`; handle cross-fs error\n   - Return `MoveResponse`\n\n5. **Modify Permissions Handler**\n   - Wildcard path; JSON body for mode\n   - `os.Stat` to get old mode\n   - `parseFileMode` for new mode\n   - `os.Chmod`; return old/new modes\n\n6. **Archive Handler** (new file)\n   - Sanitize source and dest paths\n   - Detect format from request/extension\n   - `tar.Create` or `zip.Create`\n   - Walk source; add entries with relative paths\n   - Close archive; return size\n\n7. **Extract Handler** (new file)\n   - Sanitize source; resolve dest (default parent)\n   - Open archive; iterate entries\n   - For each entry: sanitize entry path; reject escapes\n   - Create directories; write files\n   - Return extracted file list\n\n8. **Route Registration**\n   - Add DELETE, POST (directory/copy/move/archive/extract), PATCH routes\n   - All under `/api` with existing JWT auth middleware\n\n9. **Tests**\n   - Delete: file, directory (recursive/non-recursive), non-empty without flag, nonexistent\n   - Create directory: single, nested, with mode, already exists\n   - Copy: file, directory, nonexistent source, dest exists\n   - Move: file, directory, cross-directory, nonexistent source\n   - Modify permissions: file, directory, invalid mode, nonexistent\n   - Archive: tar, zip, tar.gz, large source, nonexistent source\n   - Extract: tar, zip, tar.gz, path escape in archive, large archive rejection\n\n## References\n\n- `code-execution/spec.md` — PicoD base requirements\n- `changes/AR-015/proposal.md` — Original PicoD implementation\n- `pkg/picod/files.go` — Existing file upload/list/download handlers\n- `pkg/picod/sanitize.go` — Path security logic\n- [Go archive/tar](https://pkg.go.dev/archive/tar)\n- [Go archive/zip](https://pkg.go.dev/archive/zip)"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/files.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/server.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/config.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/execute.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/sanitize.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/picod_test.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":758,"character":21},"end":{"line":758,"character":32}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/